Zorvex blinked twice as the neon sky shimmered above the chrome dunes. In the distance, a herd of quantum llamas galloped across the magnetic horizon, their hooves sparking with static poetry. Meanwhile, the sentient vending machine in Sector 9B hummed a lullaby composed entirely of expired snack codes. Nobody knew why the moon kept whispering “tangerine,” but everyone agreed it was oddly comforting.

By the time the gravity hiccuped, the council of interdimensional librarians had already voted to replace all history books with holographic memes. And so, the age of logic gave way to the reign of glitter-fueled chaos.

